  "text": "Of the 63 enrolled patients, [CITATION_1] Patients were BUS-positive. Of these, MRI results agreed with the BUS findings in 12 patients who had cortical damage of the scaphoid with hematoma. In 35 instances, hematoma with no cortical damage was detected with BUS and corroborated by MRI. A scaphoid fracture was demonstrated by MRI in two patients from this group. The sensitivity, specificity, positive predictive value, negative predictive value, and negative likelihood ratio for BUS were 85.7%, 100%, 100%, 100% and 0.14, respectively. Accuracy of BUS was not statistically different from MRI.",
